meanings.definition: To jump higher or farther than someone else.
meanings.sent1: During the race, Sarah outjumped her friend to reach the finish line first.
meanings.sent2: The athlete outjumped all his competitors in the long jump event.
meanings.sent3: The frog outjumped the rabbit in the hopping contest.
meanings.sent4: Her enthusiasm outjumped her fear, propelling her to take the leap.
meanings.sent5: With a determined look, he outjumped his previous record and landed gracefully.

meanings.definition: Past tense of outjump: to surpass in jumping ability.
meanings.sent1: Yesterday, she outjumped her own record and was thrilled with her progress.
meanings.sent2: The kangaroo outjumped the other animals in the zoo with ease.
meanings.sent3: The cat outjumped the dog, surprising everyone with its agility.
meanings.sent4: His excitement outjumped his doubts, leading him to take the risk.
meanings.sent5: The dancer outjumped her partner, showcasing her incredible skill and grace.
